https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=dlIvxxydShU&list=PLg5SS_4L6LYsxrZ_4xE_U95AtGsIB96k9&index=30

- VPC == virtual private cloud
- CIDR blocks(Classless Inter-Domain Routing): ip space available
- public subnet == direct access to internet (RDP/SSH/etc.)
- private subnet == no open access => no public ip
- database subnet
- route table == for every subnet (redirecting through path of routers)
- internet gateway => VPC has access to internet
- NAT gateway => all instances can go to internet, no public access
- NAT instance (Network Address Translation - это механизм в сетях TCP/IP, позволяющий изменять IP адрес в заголовке пакета, проходящего через устройство)
- Security Group for instances (kinda open ports)
- Network access control list == possibility to block ip address
- bastion host == jump box == kinda intermidiary service
- VPC flow logs
- VPN Gateway
- VPC peering